&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Administrator/ Receptionist (Outpatients)&lt;br /&gt; Part Time 30 Hours per week&lt;br /&gt; Fixed Term Contract to 30 September 2021&lt;br /&gt; £9.52 per hour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an Administrator/ Receptionist to join our Outstanding team, at the award winning, Benenden Hospital, set in the heart of the Kent Countryside.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our multi-million pound redevelopment means we can offer first class services in an amazing, modern environment. With an Outstanding CQC rating and a Silver award in Investors in People, you can be confident you are joining an industry leading team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require a Receptionist/ Administrator for our busy Outpatients department.&lt;br /&gt; As the first point of contact for patients, their relatives, visitors and staff arriving to the department, it is vital that you are someone that thrives in an environment where you are dealing with people both in person and over the phone. No two days are the same and where excellence in all we do is at the heart of everything we strive to achieve!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will need to implement the highest levels of customer service which includes booking appointments and admissions. We provide a warm and welcoming environment, which you will need to do whilst following strict standards. Undertaking a wide range administrative duties, you will provide link to other key areas and ensure the smooth running of the department, with Patient Care at the heart of everything.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To be considered for this role it is essential that have the following qualifications and skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Previous relevant experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Customer care qualifications or a willingness to work towards&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Excellent IT skills i.e. Microsoft Office and other relevant applications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Proven ability to undertake multiple tasks under pressure&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Excellent verbal and written communication skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Able to work effectively within a team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It would also be an advantage if you have Healthcare and APAS software experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rewards and benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Competitive salary, including an element of performance related pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          27 days annual leave entitlement plus Bank Holidays, rising with service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Generous defined contribution pension scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Excellent Life Assurance benefit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Free Membership of Benenden Health for Permanent Staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Free parking&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Subsidised eye tests&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Enhanced Maternity pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Free Flu vaccinations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Free tea and coffee&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Subsidised on site Restaurant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Cycle to work scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Active social club&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information of this role please contact Derrick Howard on 01580 857368&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Together, we work hard to maintain a safe, comfortable, patient-focused environment for the people in our care.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; All our vacancies are therefore subject to either a Standard or an Enhanced Disclosure Application to the Disclosure and Barring Service as well as satisfactory reference checks. These procedures need to be completed before a new member of staff can join the hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date 19th November&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that if a large number of applications are received this vacancy may close before the closing date without notice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), we have implemented a Privacy Notice to inform you, as prospective employees of Benenden Hospital Trust, of the types of data we process about you. Please visit our Careers page to read our Privacy Notice.&lt;/p&gt;
